#| label: random-forest-model-for-vote

load(
  here(
    "common_data/elections/aec/2022/ced_results.RData"
  )
)

ced_incumbent <- aec_data %>% 
  select(Division = DivisionNm,
         starts_with("HistoricElected")) %>% 
  mutate(inc_type = 
           case_when(
          HistoricElected_LNP == 1 ~ "Coalition",
          HistoricElected_LP == 1 ~ "Coalition",
          HistoricElected_NP == 1 ~ "Coalition",
          HistoricElected_ALP == 1 ~ "Labor",
          HistoricElected_GRN == 1 ~ "Green",
          HistoricElected_IND == 1 ~ "IND",
          TRUE ~ "Other"
          ),
         community_indep = Division %in% 
           c("Curtin",
             "Clark",
             "Indi",
             "Warringah",
             "Wentworth",
             "Mackellar",
             "North Sydney",
             "Goldstein",
             "Kooyong",
             "Cowper")
  )

load(here("common_data/surveys/aes/d2022_recoded.RData"))

library(randomForest)
d2022_tmp <- d2022 %>% 
  filter(!is.na(hvote_collapsed)) %>%
  mutate(
    CED_ABS = case_when(
      PCODE_ORIG == "0871" ~ "Lingiari",
      PCODE_ORIG == "1640" ~ "Mackellar",
      PCODE_ORIG == "8002" ~ "Melbourne",
      PCODE_ORIG == "6872" ~ "Perth",
      PCODE_ORIG == "3724" ~ "Indi",
      PCODE_ORIG == "1355" ~ "Wentworth",
      PCODE_ORIG == "0861" ~ "Lingiari",
      PCODE_ORIG == "2001" ~ "Sydney",
      TRUE ~ CED_ABS
    ),
    STATE = factor(STATE),
    PANEL = if_else(
      PANEL_FLAG == "Different person" | is.na(PANEL_FLAG),
      0,1),
    AGEP = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(AGEP,
                                          level = "NA"),
    H7 = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(H7,
                                        level = "NA"),
    
    same_sex_marriage = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(E4, level = "NA"),
    voice_to_parliament = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(E7, level = "NA"),
    global_warming = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(F9, level = "NA"),
    
    morrison_like = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(C1_1, level = "NA"),
    albo_like = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(C1_2, level = "NA"),
    
    immigrants = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(F7, level = "NA"),
    
    C6 = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(C6, level = "NA"),
    C7 = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(C7, level = "NA"),
    
    J1 = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(J1, level = "NA"),
    J2 = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(J2, level = "NA"),
    J3 = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(J3, level = "NA"),
    J4 = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(J4, level = "NA"),
    
    hvote_2019 = factor(hvote_2019),
    
    RELP_collapsed = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(RELP_collapsed,
                                                    level = "NA"),
    
    G3 = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(G3,level = "NA"),
    
    ANCP_collapse = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(ANCP_collapse,
                                                   level = "NA"),
    
    born_country_three = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(
      born_country_three,
      level = "NA"),
    
    G5Code = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(G5Code,
                                            level = "NA"),
    MSTP = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(MSTP,
                                          level = "NA"),
    
    INCP = forcats::fct_na_value_to_level(INCP,
                                          level = "NA"), 
    
  ) %>% 
  left_join(
    ced_incumbent %>% 
      select(Division,inc_type,community_indep),
    by = c("CED_ABS" = "Division")
  )
    
m <- randomForest(hvote_collapsed ~ Mode + STATE + sampsrc + 
                    PANEL + 
                    hvote_2019 + 
                    SEXP + AGEP + INCP +
                    INGP_binary + ANCP_collapse +
                    MSTP + G3 + 
                    RELP_collapsed + H7 + G5Code +
                    J1 + J2 + J3 + J4 +
                    same_sex_marriage + voice_to_parliament +
                    global_warming + 
                    immigrants + 
                    C6 + C7 + 
                    morrison_like + albo_like + 
                    PC1 + PC2 + PC3 + PC4 + PC4 + PC5 +
                    PC6 + PC7 + PC8 + PC9 + PC10 + 
                    Median_age_persons_G02 +      
                    Median_mortgage_repay_monthly_G02 +
                    Median_tot_prsnl_inc_weekly_G02 + 
                    Median_rent_weekly_G02 +          
                    Median_tot_fam_inc_weekly_G02 +   
                    Average_num_psns_per_bedroom_G02 +
                    Median_tot_hhd_inc_weekly_G02 +    
                    Average_household_size_G02 +
                    inc_type + community_indep,
                  mtry = 10,
                  data = d2022_tmp)

control <- trainControl(method = "adaptive_cv",
                        number = 5,
                        repeats = 5,
                        search = "grid",
                        allowParallel = TRUE,
                        verboseIter = TRUE)

tunegrid <- expand.grid(mtry = c(8:15,22,25)) %>%
  as.data.frame()

rf_gridsearch <- train(
  x = d2022_tmp %>%
    select(
      STATE , 
                    SEXP , AGEP , INCP ,
                    INGP_binary , ANCP_collapse , born_country_three ,
                    MSTP , G3 , 
                    RELP_collapsed , 
                    G5Code ,
                    J1 , 
                    PC1 , PC2 , PC3 , PC4 , PC4 , PC5 ,
                    PC6 , PC7 , PC8 , PC9 , PC10 , 
                    Median_age_persons_G02 ,      
                    Median_mortgage_repay_monthly_G02 ,
                    Median_tot_prsnl_inc_weekly_G02 , 
                    Median_rent_weekly_G02 ,          
                    Median_tot_fam_inc_weekly_G02 ,   
                    Average_num_psns_per_bedroom_G02 ,
                    Median_tot_hhd_inc_weekly_G02 ,    
                    Average_household_size_G02),
  y = m_2019$y,
  method = "rf",
  tuneGrid = tunegrid,
  trControl = control
)

##nrounds, max_depth, eta, gamma, subsample, colsample_bytree, rate_drop, skip_drop, min_child_weight

control <- trainControl(method = "cv",
                        number = 5,
                        repeats = 5,
                        search = "grid",
                        allowParallel = TRUE,
                        verboseIter = TRUE)

tunegrid <- expand.grid(
  nrounds = c(100,500),
  max_depth = c(4,6,8,10,12),
  eta = c(.1,.3,.5),
  gamma = 0,
  subsample = .5,
  colsample_bytree = 1,
  rate_drop = 0,
  skip_drop = 0,
  min_child_weight = c(.7, 1)
) %>%
  as.data.frame()

bm_gridsearch <- train(
  x = d2022_tmp %>%
    select(
      STATE ,
      SEXP ,
      AGEP ,
      INCP ,
      INGP_binary ,
      ANCP_collapse ,
      born_country_three ,
      MSTP ,
      G3 ,
      RELP_collapsed ,
      G5Code ,
      J1 ,
      PC1 ,
      PC2 ,
      PC3 ,
      PC4 ,
      PC4 ,
      PC5 ,
      PC6 ,
      PC7 ,
      PC8 ,
      PC9 ,
      PC10 ,
      Median_age_persons_G02 ,

      Median_tot_prsnl_inc_weekly_G02 ,
      Median_rent_weekly_G02 ,
      Median_tot_fam_inc_weekly_G02 ,
      Average_num_psns_per_bedroom_G02 ,
      Median_tot_hhd_inc_weekly_G02 ,
      Average_household_size_G02
    ),
  
  y = m_2019$y,
  tuneGrid = tunegrid,
  trControl = control,
  method = "xgbDART",
  verbose = 1,
  early_stopping_rounds = 5,
  params = list(eval_metric = merror),
)
